latest_description:
Bria Burke of Cooley is requesting a minor modification to EPLAN-2025-0149 for 22425 Sous Vide Lane, Sterling - PIN: 045-46-5016.

I am writing with regard to Loudoun County PIN 045-46-5016 (the Property), on behalf of 1501 Moran Road Development Owner LLC (the Owner), to request your offices confirmation that the minor changes proposed with the currently in-process data center site plan amendment (EPLAN-2025-0149) for the Property are permitted pursuant to Section 10.11.01.H of the Loudoun County Zoning Ordinance (the Zoning Ordinance). As is detailed in Footnote #3 to Table 3.02.05-1 of the Zoning Ordinance, a site plan amendment application for minor changes to an approved site plan for a data center use (such approved site plan being EPLAN-2023-0087 in this case) is permitted without processing a Special Exception application, so long as the proposed changes are in conformance with Section 10.11.01.H of the Zoning Ordinance. 

More specifically, Section 10.11.01.H.2. of the Zoning Ordinance states, the Zoning Administrator may permit minor changes to an approved Special Exception when such are reasonably necessary to address issues related to topography, drainage, underground utilities, structural safety, final engineering, vehicular circulation, or requirements of government agencies. As confirmed by County Staff, under this scenario, EPLAN-2023-0087 (the Approved Site Plan) operates as the approved Special Exception for purposes of Section 10. Therefore, the Owner seeks the Zoning Administrators approval of the changes described herein to the Approved Site Plan to be processed as a site plan amendment, as minor changes necessitated by issues related to topography, final engineering, and vehicular circulation. 

As detailed within the plans submitted as part of EPLAN-2025-0149, the amendment proposes to slightly adjust the location of several improvements on the Property from what was originally shown on the Approved Site Plan, including the drive aisle and the building footprint. These changes are necessary following a final engineering analysis, which determined that the retaining wall shown on the Approved Site Plan is not constructible in its initially proposed location. As a result of moving the retaining wall, the originally contemplated location of the nearby drive aisle also requires a minor relocation. A slight shift to the proposed building footprint is in turn required to accommodate the relocation of the retaining wall and drive aisle. Notably, the amendment does not seek to change the size of the building footprint or the buildings square footage.

In all, these modifications are minor in nature and will result in a more efficient and achievable layout for the Property, which is still generally consistent with the intent of the Approved Site Plan. Given the foregoing, the owner of the Property respectfully requests your offices determination that the modifications proposed with EPLAN-2025-0149 are consistent with Section 10.11.01.H of the Zoning Ordinance and that, accordingly, the site plan amendment can continue to process to final approval.

In accordance with Zoning Ordinance Section 10.11.01.H.2.b.2, prior to action on this request we will provide the Zoning Administrator with an affidavit that demonstrates that the required notice as set forth in Zoning Ordinance Section 10.11.01.H.2.b.1 has been sent.

Given EPLAN-2025-0149 is currently in-process, we would appreciate anything you can do to expediate the review and approval of this request. We will submit the Countys zoning determination request fee electronically.  Should you require any additional information, please dont hesitate to call me at (703) 456-8572. Thank you in advance for your time.

Best,
Bria

latest_description: Tenant fit-out of a 217,682 SF, 1-level Warehouse space for a Data Center. These documents entail Phase 2 of the project (Phase 1 was the shell of the building - BB-202501970). Project includes business and warehouse occupancies with an administrative area and data halls. We plan to apply for phased occupancy to allow tenant to move into areas that are completed sooner, closer to the time of occupancy.

This project was originally permitted (parent permit B20590530100) for the full fit-up of the building but due to power availability only four of the ten data halls were constructed. We are submitting for Tenant Fit -Up for the remaining six data halls. This submittal is for Phase 8 (ROMP 8). As discussed with the Building Official and County staff, these remaining phases will be applied under VA USBC-2018 codes as the standard since the base building was permitted under that code.  Architecturally the interior work typically consists of adding demising walls (metal stud and drywall) between the data halls and associated man and access doors.  Exterior architectural work is screening for equipment and setting equipment on the roof. Trade permits will be collected separately.

latest_description:
Patrick McPartland of Bowman is requesting a zoning determination for Project Aspen located at 20471 Goose Landing Lane, Leesburg - PIN: 194-49-8227. Specifically, that the proposed mechanical yard is located such that there are no adverse impacts on the adjacent properties.

2/21/2025
By way of background, the above referenced property (the Property) is split zoned 
Industrial Park (IP) and General Industry (GI) under the Loudoun County Zoning 
Ordinance. The IP portion of the Property is developed with existing data center use. 
The GI portion of the Property (Project Aspen Site) is the location of the Project 
Aspen data center that is subject to EPLAN-2024-0139 and this determination 
request. The Project Aspen Site is subject to Zoning Map Amendment (ZMAP)-2019-
0003 and Special Exception (SPEX)-2019-0003, Luck/Hayden/Loudoun Water 
Property approved February 18, 2020. EPLAN-2023-0128, Project Aspen, was 
approved November 15, 2024, for a single data center on the Project Aspen Site. 
EPLAN-2024-0139, Project Aspen, proposes a revision to approved EPLAN-2023-0128 to adjust the mechanical yard on the east side of the proposed Project Aspen data center building per new specifications provided by the Owner.

Staff notes EPLAN-2023-0128 was processed, reviewed, and approved under the land 
use and development regulations prescribed in the Revised 1993 Zoning Ordinance
pursuant to the Resolution of the Board of Supervisors of Loudoun County Virginia, 
Adopting Grandfathering Rules for ZOAM-2020-0001, Zoning Ordinance Rewrite 
(Grandfathering Resolution), adopted on December 13, 2023. EPLAN-2024-0138 is 
being processed and reviewed under the land use and development regulations 
prescribed in the Zoning Ordinance since EPLAN-2024-0138 was submitted after 
December 13, 2023 and is subject to the data center use specific standards in Zoning 
Ordinance Section 4.06.02. 

Table 4.06.02-2.b.1.d. of the Zoning Ordinance states the following:
No Screening Requirements Adjacent to Industrially Zoned Property.
As determined by the Zoning Administrator, Data Center Mechanical 
Equipment located in a manner found to have no adverse impact on adjacent 
properties zoned IP, GI, or MR-HI is not required to be screened pursuant to 
Section 4.06.02-2.b.1, except that Data Center Mechanical Equipment must 
be screened from any existing or planned public road.
Per the Countys geographic information system, WebLOGIS, the adjacent parcel 
information is as follows:
North: PIN: 152-25-4491, zoned MR-HI under the Zoning Ordinance. 
East: PIN: 152-26-8334, zoned GI under the Zoning Ordinance. 
South: PIN: 153-35-5865, zoned MR-HI under the Zoning Ordinance. 
West: PIN: 193-18-6982, zoned IP under the Zoning Ordinance. 
The adjacent parcel to the north, PIN: 152-25-4491, is currently vacant. The Project 
Aspen Site contains required buffer yard plantings as well as proffered reforestation 
area #1 along the northern property line. As such, Zoning Administration staff finds 
the mechanical equipment yard is located in a manner found to have no adverse 
impact on the adjacent parcel to the north zoned MR-HI.
The adjacent parcel to the east, PIN: 152-26-8334, is currently vacant. The Project 
Aspen Site contains a proffered Tree Conservation Area along the entirety of the 
eastern property line adjacent to PIN: 152-26-8334. As such, Zoning Administration 
staff finds the mechanical yard is located in a manner found to have no adverse 
impact on the adjacent parcel to the east zoned GI.
The adjacent parcel to the south, PIN: 153-35-5865, is currently improved with an 
existing Water Treatment Plant. Staff notes when EPLAN-2023-0128 was approved, 
a buffer yard was not required between the proposed Project Aspen data center 
(Group 10 buffer use group) and the existing Water Treatment Plant (Group 10 buffer 
use group). However, EPLAN-2023-0128 proposed to retain existing vegetation as 
Tree Conservation Area (Tree Conservation Area 3) along the southern property line 
adjacent to PIN: 153-35-5865. EPLAN-2024-0138 continues to depict Tree 
Conservation Area 3 along the southern property line adjacent to PIN: 153-35-5865. 
As such, Zoning Administration staff finds the mechanical yard is located in a manner 
found to have no adverse impact on the adjacent parcel to the south zoned MR-HI.
In regard to the visual impact on the Dulles Greenway, the southern property line of 
the Project Aspen Site adjacent to the Dulles Greenway contains a proffered Tree 
Conservation Area as depicted on Sheet 3A-C-9700 of EPLAN-2024-0139 and in line_x0002_of-sight elevation 03. Additionally, the Project Aspen Site contains proffered 
reforestation area #2 north of said proffered Tree Conservation Area. The Project 
Aspen data center building will also provide screening of the mechanical yard from 
the Dulles Greenway. As such, Zoning Administration staff finds the mechanical yard 
is sufficiently screened from the Dulles Greenway. 
The adjacent parcel to the west, PIN: 193-18-6982, has approved land development 
applications for data center development. Further, the existing data center use 
located on the IP portion of the Property is located between the Project Aspen Site 
and PIN: 193-18-6982. The Project Aspen mechanical yard is located behind the 
Project Aspen data center building to the east. As such, Zoning Administration staff 
finds the mechanical yard is located in a manner found to have no adverse impact on 
the adjacent property to the west zoned IP.
